OL,3,CMore than #13bn promised for infected
OL,4,Cblood and Horizon scandal victims
OL,6,FThose wrongfully convicted are
OL,7,Feligible for compensation, along with
OL,8,Fmore than 2,750 subpostmasters who
OL,9,Fhave been affected by the scandal but
OL,10,Fnot convicted.
OL,12,FThe larger sum of money is being set
OL,13,Faside for the infected blood scandal,
OL,14,Fwhich has been labelled the "worst
OL,15,Ftreatment disaster in the NHS."
OL,17,FBetween 1970 and 1991 it's thought up
OL,18,Fto 30,000 people were infected with
OL,19,FHIV and Hepatitis C after they were
OL,20,Ftreated with contaminated blood often
OL,21,Fbought from the US.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
