OL,3,CMore than #13bn promised for infected
OL,4,Cblood and Horizon scandal victims
OL,6,FThose affected by the scandal are
OL,7,Fsplit into two groups.
OL,9,FThe first group are people with
OL,10,Fhaemophilia - experts believe 1,250
OL,11,Fpeople contracted HIV and Hepatitis C.
OL,13,FTwo-thirds then died of AIDS-related
OL,14,Fillnesses, with an unknown amount
OL,15,Ftransferring HIV to their partners.
OL,17,FThe second group were those given
OL,18,Fblood transfusions after childbirth or
OL,19,Fsurgery - 27,000 of whom were infected
OL,20,Fwith Hepatitis C.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
